magpie.data.utilities.splitters

Class NonZeroClassificationSplitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.splitters.BaseDatasetSplitter
      • magpie.data.utilities.splitters.NonZeroClassificationSplitter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Commandable, Options, Printable

    public class NonZeroClassificationSplitter
extends BaseDatasetSplitter
    Split data based on whether an entry is likely to have a non-zero class variable. If the probability of the entry having a class variable equal to zero is past a certain threshold, it is assigned to subset #0.

    Usage: <threshold> $<model>
    threshold: Probability of having a class == 0 on which to split
    model: AbstractClassifier to use for partitioning data. Must distinguish between two classes

    See Also:
